codex
Ranked hypotheses for the red loop:

1. The fixture omits `X-Request-ID` on both send and complete; the new exact-audit predicate requires a non-empty retained request context, so both otherwise-valid actions are deliberately non-current.
2. The fixture’s communication/task defaults differ from the new exact delivery ledger.
3. The fixture’s role/team facts changed between action time and readiness evaluation.
4. Documentation setup creates a duplicate SAP-related ledger sibling.

Prediction for #1: adding explicit, distinct request IDs to only those two existing HTTP actions will make the exact same readiness flow green with no production relaxation. I’ll verify the API contract’s request-ID rule, then test that one-variable change.
